text: Yendy Cortinas (born 4 July 1972) is a Mexican volleyball player. She played at the 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2003 Women's Pan- American Volleyball Cup, 2006 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2006 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, and 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. She played for Club Voleibol Benidorm and Coahuila. == References == Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican volleyball players
